          ],
          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# Step 4: Range-Doppler — full view + range-only adaptive-x crop in ONE block,\n# faithful (surface3d_pair_gl, NO max-pool). Vertical axis is Doppler [Hz] (not\n# metres): only the range axis is cropped AND complex-upsampled by F to maximize\n# range detail. The crop title/status note the (range) upsample factor. Toggle\n# Full/Crop.\nrg_axis = (t_r - t_r_center) * c / 2\n_W = float(view_scale)\n\n_rc = np.where((rg_axis >= -_W) & (rg_axis <= _W))[0]\n_sub = S_rd[:, _rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1]\n_rgx = rg_axis[_rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1]\nF = crop_upsample_factor(S_rd.shape[0], len(_rgx), range_only=True)\n_mag = upsample_complex_range(_sub, F)\n_rgu = upsample_axis(_rgx, F)\n\nsurface3d_pair_gl(\n    S_rd, rg_axis, f_eta, 'Step 4: Range-Doppler (full view)',\n    _mag, _rgu, f_eta, 'Step 4: Range-Doppler (range x%d crop)' % F,\n    ylabel_a='Doppler [Hz]', ylabel_b='Doppler [Hz]',\n    status_b='upsample x%d (range)' % F)",
            "label": "Plot: Range-Doppler",
            "spec": "Display-only: 3-D dB surface of |S_rd| in the Range-Doppler domain. A target's energy lies on the RCM parabola (curved ridge across range vs Doppler) — this is why RCMC is needed. Axes: range [m] x Doppler [Hz]. Full resolution (no downsampling); the Crop view is range-upsampled. Toggle Full/Crop."
          },
          "codeCollapsed": true,
          "enabled": false
        },
        "width": 400,
